---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';

// Page meta
const title = "Ethics & Sustainability";
const description = "Ethical considerations and sustainability aspects of our fake news detection research.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="bg-neutral-50 py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <SectionHeader 
        title="Ethics & Sustainability"
        subtitle="Exploring the ethical implications and long-term sustainability of fake news detection systems"
      />
      
      <!-- Ethical Considerations -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-6">Ethical Considerations</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <!-- Data Privacy -->
          <Card title="Data Privacy" icon="🔒" borderColor="border-primary-300" hoverEffect={true}>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Collection and Usage</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
              Our research involves processing large volumes of news content, which raises important privacy considerations.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Only publicly available news articles used</li>
              <li>No personal user data collected or processed</li>
              <li>Data anonymization when applicable</li>
              <li>Secure storage of training datasets</li>
              <li>Transparent data handling policies</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-neutral-100 p-3 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 italic">
                "Privacy by design" principles are integrated into our system architecture
                to ensure responsible data handling throughout the research process.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Card>
          
          <!-- Algorithmic Bias -->
          <Card title="Algorithmic Bias" icon="⚖️" borderColor="border-primary-300" hoverEffect={true}>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Bias Mitigation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
              Machine learning models can inadvertently learn and amplify biases present in training data.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Diverse and balanced training datasets</li>
              <li>Regular bias audits and evaluations</li>
              <li>Topic-balanced test cases</li>
              <li>Avoidance of politically charged features</li>
              <li>Continuous monitoring for unfair classifications</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-neutral-100 p-3 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 italic">
                We continuously evaluate our system to identify and mitigate potential biases
                that could affect specific topics, sources, or viewpoints.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Card>
          
          <!-- Freedom of Expression -->
          <Card title="Freedom of Expression" icon="🗣️" borderColor="border-primary-300" hoverEffect={true}>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Supporting Free Speech</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
              Fake news detection systems must balance misinformation control with respecting free expression.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Transparent classification criteria</li>
              <li>Focus on factual accuracy, not ideological content</li>
              <li>Avoidance of censorship mechanisms</li>
              <li>Clear distinction between opinion and falsehood</li>
              <li>User empowerment through information, not restriction</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-neutral-100 p-3 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 italic">
                Our system is designed to inform, not censor, allowing users to make
                their own decisions about content while providing factual context.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Card>
          
          <!-- Accountability -->
          <Card title="Accountability" icon="📋" borderColor="border-primary-300" hoverEffect={true}>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Responsible Development</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
              Establishing clear accountability for system decisions and impacts.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Clear governance framework</li>
              <li>Transparent decision-making processes</li>
              <li>Regular error analysis and reporting</li>
              <li>Feedback mechanisms for misclassifications</li>
              <li>Independent auditing when deployed at scale</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-neutral-100 p-3 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 italic">
                We maintain clear documentation of system limitations and potential
                failure modes to ensure responsible implementation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Card>
          
          <!-- Power Dynamics -->
          <Card title="Power Dynamics" icon="🔄" borderColor="border-primary-300" hoverEffect={true}>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Balancing Control</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
              Addressing the implications of who controls the definition of "truth" in automated systems.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Multi-stakeholder governance models</li>
              <li>Diverse development team composition</li>
              <li>Cultural and political diversity in training</li>
              <li>Transparent classification criteria</li>
              <li>Prioritization of verifiable facts over interpretation</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-neutral-100 p-3 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 italic">
                We acknowledge the power inherent in defining "fake news" and strive
                for inclusive, diverse, and transparent approaches to truth verification.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Card>
          
          <!-- Transparency -->
          <Card title="Transparency" icon="🔍" borderColor="border-primary-300" hoverEffect={true}>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Explainable AI</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
              Making classification decisions understandable and verifiable.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
              <li>Feature importance visualization</li>
              <li>User-friendly explanation of decisions</li>
              <li>Open methodology documentation</li>
              <li>Highlighting of potentially problematic content</li>
              <li>Confidence scores with all predictions</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-neutral-100 p-3 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 italic">
                Our focus on interpretable models like logistic regression supports transparency
                by making classification decisions more understandable to users.
              </p>
            </div>
          </Card>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Sustainability Aspects -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-6">Sustainability Aspects</h3>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <!-- Environmental Impact -->
          <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="p-3 bg-primary-100 text-primary-700 rounded-full flex-shrink-0">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3.055 11H5a2 2 0 012 2v1a2 2 0 002 2 2 2 0 012 2v2.945M8 3.935V5.5A2.5 2.5 0 0010.5 8h.5a2 2 0 012 2 2 2 0 104 0 2 2 0 012-2h1.064M15 20.488V18a2 2 0 012-2h3.064M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-3">Environmental Impact</h4>
                
                <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
                  The computational resources required for training and deploying machine learning models
                  have significant environmental implications.
                </p>
                
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <div class="bg-neutral-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h5 class="font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Carbon Footprint</h5>
                    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">
                      Training large ML models requires significant computational resources, resulting
                      in energy consumption and carbon emissions. Our current approach using simpler models
                      like Logistic Regression offers a more environmentally sustainable alternative to
                      resource-intensive deep learning models.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="bg-neutral-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h5 class="font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Efficiency Measures</h5>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li>Optimized feature selection to reduce dimensionality</li>
                      <li>Model compression techniques when applicable</li>
                      <li>Efficient batch processing for training</li>
                      <li>Green cloud providers for deployment</li>
                      <li>Regular efficiency audits and optimizations</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-6 flex items-center justify-between">
                  <div class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Current Model</div>
                  <div class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Large Deep Learning</div>
                </div>
                <div class="w-full bg-neutral-200 rounded-full h-2.5 mb-4">
                  <div class="bg-green-500 h-2.5 rounded-full" style="width: 25%"></div>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
                  Estimated carbon footprint comparison: Our current approach uses approximately 25% of the energy
                  required by large transformer-based models.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Social Sustainability -->
          <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-300">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="p-3 bg-primary-100 text-primary-700 rounded-full flex-shrink-0">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4.354a4 4 0 110 5.292M15 21H3v-1a6 6 0 0112 0v1zm0 0h6v-1a6 6 0 00-9-5.197M13 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-3">Social Sustainability</h4>
                
                <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
                  The long-term social implications of automated content classification systems
                  must be carefully considered and managed.
                </p>
                
                <div class="space-y-4">
                  <div class="bg-neutral-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h5 class="font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Information Ecosystem</h5>
                    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">
                      Fake news detection systems can contribute to healthier information ecosystems
                      by reducing the spread of misinformation. However, they must be deployed thoughtfully
                      to avoid creating new forms of information inequality or reinforcing existing power structures.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="bg-neutral-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    <h5 class="font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Inclusive Development</h5>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li>Multi-stakeholder input in system design</li>
                      <li>Accessibility for diverse user groups</li>
                      <li>Consideration of global contexts, not just Western perspectives</li>
                      <li>Educational components to build media literacy</li>
                      <li>Open access to research findings and methodologies</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="mt-6 bg-neutral-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h5 class="font-medium text-neutral-800 mb-2">Trust Building</h5>
                  <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">
                    Sustainable fake news detection requires building trust with users and
                    stakeholders. This includes:
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1 mt-2">
                    <li>Transparency about system limitations</li>
                    <li>Clear error correction processes</li>
                    <li>User feedback incorporation</li>
                    <li>Regular performance auditing</li>
                    <li>Educational resources about how classifications work</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Ethical Framework -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-6">Ethical Framework</h3>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            Based on our exploration of ethical considerations, we've developed a comprehensive
            framework to guide the responsible development and deployment of fake news detection systems:
          </p>
          
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-6">
            <!-- Principle 1 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-2">Accuracy and Transparency</h4>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">
                Strive for the highest possible classification accuracy while maintaining
                complete transparency about methods, limitations, and confidence levels.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Principle 2 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-2">Fairness and Inclusivity</h4>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">
                Ensure equitable treatment across diverse topics, viewpoints, and cultural contexts,
                avoiding bias against specific groups or perspectives.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Principle 3 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-2">Privacy and Data Protection</h4>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">
                Respect user privacy and data rights through responsible data collection,
                storage, and processing practices.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Principle 4 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-2">Human Autonomy</h4>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">
                Support human decision-making rather than replacing it, providing information
                that empowers users to make their own informed judgments.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Principle 5 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-2">Continuous Improvement</h4>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">
                Commit to ongoing evaluation, error analysis, and system refinement to address
                emerging challenges and improve performance.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Principle 6 -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-4">
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-700 mb-2">Educational Approach</h4>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">
                Provide educational context alongside classifications to help users
                understand not just what content might be false, but why it's been flagged.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Implementation Framework -->
          <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-4">Implementation Safeguards</h4>
            
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-neutral-200">
                <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
                  <tr>
                    <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Stage</th>
                    <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Ethical Safeguards</th>
                    <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Implementation Methods</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="bg-white divide-y divide-neutral-200">
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-800">Data Collection</td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Privacy protection</li>
                        <li>Diverse representation</li>
                        <li>Balanced datasets</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Public domain sources only</li>
                        <li>Demographic auditing</li>
                        <li>Topic balancing algorithms</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-800">Model Development</td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Bias mitigation</li>
                        <li>Environmental efficiency</li>
                        <li>Interpretability</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Regular bias testing</li>
                        <li>Optimized training procedures</li>
                        <li>Feature importance analysis</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-800">Deployment</td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>User autonomy</li>
                        <li>Transparency</li>
                        <li>Feedback mechanisms</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Informative rather than restrictive UX</li>
                        <li>Confidence score visualization</li>
                        <li>User-friendly correction tools</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-800">Ongoing Operation</td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Regular auditing</li>
                        <li>Error analysis</li>
                        <li>Independent oversight</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                    <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
                        <li>Quarterly performance reviews</li>
                        <li>Public error reporting</li>
                        <li>External ethics committee</li>
                      </ul>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            
            <p class="mt-6 text-neutral-700 italic text-center">
              "In combating fake news, we must be vigilant not to create new problems while solving existing ones.
              Ethical considerations are not secondary concerns but central to effective system design."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>